tags: ["PYQ", "FMGE Jul 2025"],
text: "A girl with a history of contact lens use presents with eye pain and decreased vision. She does not follow proper lens hygiene. Which of the following organisms is the most likely causative agent?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Acanthamoeba", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "Herpes simplex", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Fungal ulcer", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Pneumococcus", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "**Acanthamoeba keratitis** is a severe corneal infection classically associated with contact lens use and poor hygiene.<br><br>* Severe pain disproportionate to findings\n* Redness, photophobia, decreased vision\n* Ring-shaped corneal infiltrate (late finding)\n<br><br><br>**Risk factors:**<br><br>* Improper lens cleaning\n* Exposure to contaminated water (tap water, swimming)\n<br><br><br>**Clinical importance:** Often misdiagnosed early \u2192 can lead to vision loss<br><br>**Why not others:**\n**B. Herpes simplex** \u2192 dendritic ulcer, \u2193 corneal sensation\n**C. Fungal** \u2192 vegetative trauma, feathery margins\n**D. Pneumococcus** \u2192 bacterial ulcer, not linked to lenses",
