explanation: "Acanthamoeba keratitis is a severe, vision-threatening corneal infection classically associated with contact lens use, especially with poor hygiene or exposure to contaminated water.<br><br>* Severe pain disproportionate to clinical findings (hallmark)\n* Redness, photophobia, \u2193 vision\n* Ring-shaped corneal infiltrate (late sign)\n* History of contact lens use / water exposure\n<br><br><br>Pathogenesis:<br><br>* Free-living protozoa (Acanthamoeba) invade cornea\n* Often introduced via contaminated lens solutions or water\n<br><br><br>Why not others:<br><br>* Staphylococcus / Streptococcus: Cause bacterial keratitis but pain is not disproportionately severe\n* Listeria: Rare ocular infection, not typical in contact lens users",
