explanation: "Episcleritis is a benign, self-limiting inflammation of the episclera presenting with a localized nodular redness near the limbus, mild discomfort, and rapid response to topical therapy.<br><br>* Sectoral or nodular redness near limbus\n* Mild pain or discomfort (not severe)\n* No significant vision loss\n* Vessels are superficial and mobile\n* Blanch with phenylephrine<br><br>\nAssociation: Can be associated with systemic diseases, especially rheumatoid arthritis, but often idiopathic<br><br>Why not others:<br><br>* Scleritis: Severe pain, deep violaceous redness, does not blanch, vision-threatening\n* Pinguecula: Yellowish degenerative lesion, non-inflammatory\n* Pterygium: Fibrovascular growth crossing cornea",
