explanation: "Intracorneal ring segments (Intacs) are used in the management of keratoconus, a progressive corneal ectasia.<br><br>* Intacs are placed in the corneal stroma\n* They flatten and regularize the corneal curvature\n* Improve irregular astigmatism and visual acuity\n<br><br><br>Indications:<br><br>* Mild to moderate keratoconus\n* Contact lens intolerance\n* Alternative to delay or avoid keratoplasty<br><br>Often combined with corneal collagen cross-linking (CXL) for stabilization<br><br>Why not others:<br><br>* Cataract: Treated with lens extraction\n* Corneal ulcer: Treated medically (antibiotics/antifungals)\n* Glaucoma: Managed with medications/surgery affecting aqueous outflow<br><br>",
