text: "A patient presents with the ocular deviation as shown in the image. What is the degree of deviation?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "90 PD Esotropia", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "90 PD Exotropia", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "C", "text": "90 degree Esotropia", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "90 degree Exotropia", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "**Ocular deviation is quantified in prism diopters (PD), not degrees.**<br><br>* Exotropia = outward deviation of the eye\n* Esotropia = inward deviation\n<br><br><br>A deviation of 90 PD exotropia represents a large-angle outward squint, commonly seen in conditions like long-standing sensory strabismus or third nerve palsy.<br><br>**Key concept:**<br><br>* 1 PD = deviation of 1 cm at 1 meter\n* Clinical measurement of strabismus is always expressed in prism diopters, not degrees",
